    history "Good morning class. I will be teaching you about \"The Plague\". While it is referred to universally as just \"The Plague\", it has other names such as \"The Pink Death\", \"The Pink Plague\" and \"The Miasma\"."
    history "During this class we will learn about only the factual information of The Plague and try to avoid a lot of the propaganda or conspiracy theories. Although some of that is still important information since it dictated people's actions during the initial outbreak."
    history "First important thing to know is that The Plague is not related to COVID-19 or the Coronavirus. While it will come up during our discussions, they are two entirely different pandemics."
    history "Coronavirus as you can guess by the name, is a virus. While the Pink Plague is a bacteria."
    history "Second, you will of course ask where it came from or how it started. And the most accurate answer I can give is, \"I don't know\". The most dominant theory is that it started somewhere around the Mediterranean."
    history "Next lesson we will discuss how many were infected and its death toll."
