    history "While the checkpoints and walls around major population centres were put up to keep the spread of the Plague out, these walls are now maintained for security purposes."
    history "Initially some of the smaller communities lived just outside the walls and even built smaller settlements as an extension of the walls. But that didn't end well..."
    history "Constant attacks on the supply convoys, the spread of the Plague and the constant attempts to breach the walls lead to what is known in [town] as \"the burning\"."
