    history "Not just the shanty towns that developed outside, but everything was burned. Trees and buildings were burned to ash along with the settlements to force any squatters to disperse further from [town]."
    history "Right now if you looked over one of the walls, there is a wasteland for a few hundred meters where everything burned. Making sure no one can live close to, plan ambushes or spy on things nearby the walls."
    history "This of course means [town] as well as the other cities have an extremely hostile relationship with the settlements out there. Combine that with the rampant Plague spread for the settlements, it has lead to an attack on sight policy."
